<title>JAPAN: SHOWA SHELL TO SHUT KAWASAKI TOPPER FROM SEPT 2.</title>
<headline>SHOWA SHELL TO SHUT KAWASAKI TOPPER FROM SEPT 2.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-08-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>Showa Shell Sekiyu KK said on Tuesday it would close the 120,000 barrel-per-day crude distillation unit (CDU) at its Kawasaki plant near Tokyo from September 2 for maintenance checks.</p>
<p>The unit is expected to resume operations on October 7.</p>
<p>Closure schedules for secondary units at the plant are as follows:</p>
<p>Facility			Capacity	     Date</p>
<p>			   (barrels per day)</p>
<p>Vacuum distillation unit   30,000	Aug 30 to Oct 10</p>
<p>Catalytic reformer	   21,500	Sep  1 to Oct  7</p>
<p>				    6,000	Sep  1 to Oct  7</p>
<p>Naphtha desulphuriser	28,000	Sep  1 to Oct  7</p>
<p>Kerosene/gas oil</p>
<p>    desulphuriser	    21,000	Aug 31 to Oct  8</p>
<p>				   27,000	Aug 31 to Oct  8</p>
<p>Indirect desulphuriser     16,000	Aug 30 to Oct 11</p>
<p>Showa Shell Sekiyu is owned 50 percent by the Royal Dutch/Shell Group.</p>
<p>-- Tokyo Energy Desk (81) 3-3432-8837</p>
